variant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mrow></msub></math><br />(iv) <math><mn>2</mn><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#8652;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mtext>RT</mtext></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mtext>RT</mtext></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mrow></msub></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28034,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["\\(\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{\\mathrm{RT}}}\\)","\\((\\mathrm{RT})^{1 / 2}\\)","\\(\\mathrm{RT}\\)","1"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{CO}(\\mathrm{g})+\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{O}_2(\\mathrm{~g}) \\rightleftharpoons \\mathrm{CO}_2(\\mathrm{~g}) \\\\ & \\Delta \\mathrm{n}_{\\mathrm{g}}=1-\\left(1+\\frac{1}{2}\\right)=-\\frac{1}{2} \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{K}_{\\mathrm{p}}}{\\mathrm{K}_{\\mathrm{C}}}=(\\mathrm{RT})^{\\Delta \\mathrm{n}_{\\mathrm{g}}}=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{\\mathrm{RT}}}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28068,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><msup><mfenced><mi>RT</mi></mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></msub><mi>RT</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>47</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>083</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>288</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (22 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28013,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Let the initial moles of $N_2O_5$ be $2$.<br><br>The given reaction is:<br>$2N_2O_5(g) \\rightleftharpoons 2N_2O_4(g) + O_2(g)$<br><br>Since $N_2O_5$ is $50\\%$ dissociated (degree of dissociation $\\alpha = 0.5$), the moles at equilibrium are:<br>Moles of $N_2O_5 = 2(1 - 0.5) = 1$<br>Moles of $N_2O_4 = 2(0.5) = 1$<br>Moles of $O_2 = 0.5$<br><br>Total moles at equilibrium $= 1 + 1 + 0.5 = 2.5$<br><br>Given the total pressure $P = 2$ atm, the partial pressures of the gases are:<br>$P_{N_2O_5} = \\dfrac{1}{2.5} \\times 2 = 0.8$ atm<br>$P_{N_2O_4} = \\dfrac{1}{2.5} \\times 2 = 0.8$ atm<br>$P_{O_2} = \\dfrac{0.5}{2.5} \\times 2 = 0.4$ atm<br><br>The equilibrium constant $K_p$ is:<br>$K_p = \\dfrac{(P_{N_2O_4})^2 \\cdot P_{O_2}}{(P_{N_2O_5})^2} = \\dfrac{(0.8)^2 \\times 0.4}{(0.8)^2} = 0.4$<br><br>The standard free energy change $\\Delta G^\\circ$ is given by:<br>$\\Delta G^\\circ = -RT \\ln K_p$<br><br>Using the given values:<br>$\\ln(0.4) = 2.303 \\log(0.4) = 2.303 (\\log 4 - \\log 10)$<br>$\\ln(0.4) = 2.303 (2 \\log 2 - 1) = 2.303 (2 \\times 0.30 - 1) = 2.303 (-0.4) = -0.9212$<br><br>Now, substituting the values into the $\\Delta G^\\circ$ equation ($T = 50^\\circ C + 273 = 323$ K):<br>$\\Delta G^\\circ = -8.314 \\times 323 \\times (-0.9212)$<br>$\\Delta G^\\circ = 2473.81$ J mol$^{-1}$<br><br>The magnitude of the standard free energy change to the nearest integer is $2474$ J mol$^{-1}$.<br><br>Answer: $2474$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (04 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28129,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{N}_2(\\mathrm{~g})+\\mathrm{O}_2(\\mathrm{~g}) \\rightleftharpoons 2 \\mathrm{NO}(\\mathrm{g})$","$\\mathrm{PCl}_5(\\mathrm{~g}) \\rightleftharpoons \\mathrm{PCl}_3(\\mathrm{~g})+\\mathrm{Cl}_2(\\mathrm{~g})$","$\\mathrm{N}_2(\\mathrm{~g})+3 \\mathrm{H}_2(\\mathrm{~g}) \\rightleftharpoons 2 \\mathrm{NH}_3(\\mathrm{~g})$","$\\mathrm{SO}_2 \\mathrm{Cl}_2(\\mathrm{~g}) \\rightleftharpoons \\mathrm{SO}_2(\\mathrm{~g})+\\mathrm{Cl}_2(\\mathrm{~g})$"],"answer":0,"solution":"In this reaction the ratio of number of moles of reactants to products is same i.e. 2 : 2, hence change in volume will not alter the number of moles.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":28122,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["exothermic","endothermic","one with negligible enthalpy change","highly spontaneous at ordinary temperature"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{K}_{\\mathrm{eq}}=\\mathrm{A} \\mathrm{e}^{-\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{H}}{\\mathrm{RT}}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":28036,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["Addition of \\(\\mathrm{CO}_2\\)","Removal of \\(\\mathrm{CO}_2\\)","Addition of \\(\\mathrm{Fe}_2 \\mathrm{O}_3\\)","Removal of CO"],"answer":2,"solution":"When solid added no effect on equilibrium.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28094,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["$4 \\mathrm{NH}_3(\\mathrm{g})+5 \\mathrm{O}_2(\\mathrm{g}) \\rightleftharpoons 4 \\mathrm{NO}$ (g) $+6 \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}(\\mathrm{l})$","$2 \\mathrm{NO}_2(\\mathrm{g}) \\rightleftharpoons 2 \\mathrm{NO}(\\mathrm{g})+\\mathrm{O}_2$ (g)","$3 \\mathrm{O}_2 \\rightleftharpoons 2 \\mathrm{O}_3(\\mathrm{g})$","$\\mathrm{H}_2(\\mathrm{g})+\\mathrm{I}_2(\\mathrm{g}) \\rightleftharpoons 2 \\mathrm{HI}(\\mathrm{g})$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Volume $\\uparrow P \\downarrow$, reaction proceeds in which direction where the number of moles of gases increases.\n$2 \\mathrm{NO}_2(\\mathrm{~g}) \\rightleftharpoons 2 \\mathrm{NO}(\\mathrm{g})+\\mathrm{O}_2(\\mathrm{~g})$\n$\\Delta \\mathrm{n}_{\\mathrm{g}}=(2+1)-2=1$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":28090,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>24</mn><mo>.63</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msup><mi>dm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mi>atm</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>606</mn><mo>.0&#160;</mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mi>atm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>.65</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>atm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>mol</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>,24.62&#160;</mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mi>atm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>606</mn><mo>.0&#160;</mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mi>atm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>,24.62&#160;</mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mi>atm</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>.65</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>atm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>mol</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>, 4.1</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>atm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mi>mol</mi><mo>,</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>606</mn><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msup><mi>dm</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mi>atm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8757;</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>RT</mi></mfenced><mi>&#916;ng</mi></msup></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>RT</mi></mfenced><mi>&#916;ng</mi></msup></math><br /><br />(i)&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8652;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>NO</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi>&#916;ng</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8756;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math><br /><br />(ii)&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>&#8652;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>Na</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>&#916;ng</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>&#8756;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>RT</mi></mfenced><mn>1</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>.62</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>1</mn></msup></math><br /><br />(iii)&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8652;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>&#916;ng</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>RT</mi></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>.62</mo></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.659</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math><math> <mrow> <mo>&#8771;</mo><mn>1.65</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup> <mrow> <mn>10</mn></mrow> <mrow> <mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow> </msup> </mrow> </math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28025,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"\\(\\begin{array}{llll} <br />& \\mathrm{CO}(\\mathrm{g}) & + & 2 \\mathrm{H}_2(\\mathrm{g}) & \\rightleftharpoons & \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{OH}(\\mathrm{g}) \\\\<br>\\mathrm{t}=0 & 0.1 \\mathrm{~mol} & & \\mathrm{a} \\mathrm{~mol} & & - \\\\<br>\\mathrm{t}_{\\text {eq }} & 0.1-\\mathrm{x} & & \\mathrm{a}-2 \\mathrm{x} & & \\mathrm{x}=0.04 \\\\<br>& =0.06 & & =\\mathrm{a}-0.08 & \\\\<br>& & & =0.23-0.08 \\\\<br>& & & =0.15 \\mathrm{~mole}<br />\\end{array}\\)<br />\\(\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{V}=2 \\mathrm{~L} \\\\ & \\mathrm{~T}=500 \\mathrm{~K} \\\\ & \\mathrm{P}_{\\text {total }}=5 \\mathrm{bar} \\\\ & \\mathrm{n}_{\\text {Total }}=0.25=\\frac{1}{4} \\mathrm{~mol} \\\\ & \\mathrm{P}_{\\text {total }}=\\mathrm{n}_{\\text {total }} \\times \\frac{\\mathrm{RT}}{\\mathrm{V}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow 5=(0.06+\\mathrm{a}-0.08+0.04) \\times \\frac{0.08 \\times 500}{2} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow 10=(0.02+\\mathrm{a}) \\times 0.08 \\times 500\\end{aligned}\\)<br />\\(\\Rightarrow \\mathrm{a}=0.25-0.02=0.23 \\mathrm{~mol}.\\)<br />\\(\\begin{aligned}<br />& \\mathrm{K}_{\\mathrm{P}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{OH}}}{\\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{CO}} \\times \\mathrm{X}_{\\mathrm{H}_2}^2} \\times \\frac{1}{\\left(\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{T}}\\right)^2}=\\frac{0.04}{0.06 \\times(0.15)^2} \\times\\left[\\frac{1 / 4}{5}\\right]^2 \\\\<br>& =\\frac{4}{6 \\times(0.15)^2 \\times 16} \\times \\frac{1}{25} \\\\<br>& =\\frac{100 \\times 100}{24 \\times 225 \\times 25}=\\frac{100 \\times 100}{135000} \\\\<br>& =0.074=74 \\times 10^{-3}<br />\\end{aligned}\\)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (2 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28017,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"The equilibrium constant for the reaction $X_2(g) + Y_2(g) \\rightleftharpoons 2Z(g)$ is calculated from the initial equilibrium state:<br>$K_c = \\frac{[Z]^2}{[X_2][Y_2]} = \\frac{9^2}{3 \\times 3} = 9$ mol/L.<br>When 10 mol of Z(g) is added, the new concentrations are: $[X_2] = 3$, $[Y_2] = 3$, $[Z] = 19$ mol.<br>The reaction quotient is $Q = \\frac{19^2}{3 \\times 3} = 40.11$.<br>Since $Q > K_c$, the equilibrium shifts left (toward reactants).<br>Let $x$ mol of Z decompose. At the new equilibrium: $[X_2] = 3 + \\frac{x}{2}$, $[Y_2] = 3 + \\frac{x}{2}$, $[Z] = 19 - x$.<br>Applying the equilibrium expression: $\\frac{(19-x)^2}{(3+\\frac{x}{2})^2} = 9$.<br>Taking the square root: $\\frac{19-x}{3+\\frac{x}{2}} = 3$.<br>Solving: $19 - x = 9 + \\frac{3x}{2}$, which gives $10 = \\frac{5x}{2}$, so $x = 4$.<br>The moles of Z at new equilibrium = $19 - 4 = 15$ mol.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28045,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mrow><msub><mi>PCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></munder><mo>+</mo><munder><mrow><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><munder><mo>&#8652;</mo><mrow></mrow></munder><munder><mrow><msub><mi>PCl</mi><mn>5</mn></msub><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></munder></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></math></p><p>If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math> moles of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> is added. When reactant is added the reaction takes place in forward direction.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>20</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>&#177;</mo><msqrt><mn>121</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>64</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>40</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>55</mn></mrow><mn>40</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8771;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08625</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><msub><mi>PCl</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>48625</mn><mo>&#8771;</mo><mn>48</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>625</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>49</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (06 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28091,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["Sodium tetra borate","Ferrous Ammonium sulphate","Oxalic acid","Dil. HCl"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>A&nbsp;<b>primary standard</b>&nbsp;in metrology is a standard&nbsp;that is sufficiently accurate such that it is not calibrated by or subordinate to other standards. Primary standards are defined via other quantities like length, mass&nbsp;and time. Primary standards are used to calibrate other standards referred to as working standards.</p><p>Oxalic acid is used as a primary standard for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>NaOH</mi></math> standardization.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (16 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":28119,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{K}_1 \\sqrt{\\mathrm{K}_2}=\\mathrm{K}_3$","$\\mathrm{K}_2 \\mathrm{~K}_3=\\mathrm{K}_1$","$\\mathrm{K}_3=\\mathrm{K}_1 \\mathrm{~K}_2$","$\\mathrm{K}_3 \\cdot \\mathrm{K}_2^3=\\mathrm{K}_1^2$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Equation (c) = equation (a) + equation (b)\nThus $\\mathrm{K}_3=\\mathrm{K}_1 \\cdot \\mathrm{K}_2$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2008","image":null},{"id":28015,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["$0.53,0.4$.","$0.742,0.557$.","$0.557,0.418$.","$0.367,0.275$."],"answer":2,"solution":"Initial equilibrium:<br>[A]=0.5 M, [B]=0.375 M; $K_c=\\frac{0.375}{0.5}=0.75$<br>After adding 0.1 mol A: [A]=0.6 M, [B]=0.375 M; Q=0.625<br>Q < Kc, so equilibrium shifts right.<br>Let x be A that decomposes:<br>$\\frac{0.375+x}{0.6-x}=0.75$<br>0.375+x=0.45-0.75x<br>1.75x=0.075; x≈0.0429<br>New [A]=0.6-0.0429=0.557 M; [B]=0.375+0.0429=0.418 M","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28097,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["<math><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>19</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>21</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>HCl</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8594;</mo></mtd><mtd><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mtd><mtd><mo>+</mo></mtd><mtd><msup><mi>Cl</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8652;</mo></mtd><mtd><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mtd><mtd><mo>+</mo></mtd><mtd><msup><mi>HS</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mtd><mtd></mtd><mtd><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi></mrow></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mn>1</mn></msu